@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam maxMessageSize 140
skinparam wrapWidth 220

title EduSecure Space Chat E2EE Flow (Implemented)

actor "Manager" as Manager
actor "Recipient" as Recipient
participant "Manager Browser" as ManagerBrowser
participant "Recipient Browser" as RecipientBrowser
participant "SpaceChatPanel" as Panel
participant "spaceChatService" as ChatApi
participant "SpaceChatE2eeController" as E2eeController
participant "SpaceChatE2eeService" as E2eeService
participant "SpaceChatController" as ChatController
participant "MongoSpaceChatService" as ChatService
collections "IndexedDB\nchatKeyStore" as KeyStore
collections "PostgreSQL\nuser_chat_keys\nspace_chat_key_versions\nspace_chat_key_recipients" as PG
collections "MongoDB\nspace_chat_messages" as Mongo

note right of Panel
Implemented crypto stack:
- ECDH P-256 device keys
- SHA-256 public-key fingerprint
- AES-GCM 256 room keys
- ECDH + HKDF-SHA-256 wrap-key derivation
- AES-GCM message encryption
- base64url for nonce/ciphertext fields
end note

group 1. Browser key registration
Manager -> ManagerBrowser : open SpaceDetail / chat panel
ManagerBrowser -> Panel : setupEncryptedChatOnThisDevice()
Panel -> Panel : detectBrowserCryptoSupport()
Panel -> Panel : generateChatKeyPairMaterial()
note right of Panel
Frontend generates an ECDH P-256 key pair.
Public JWK is canonicalized and fingerprinted
with SHA-256.
end note
Panel -> KeyStore : saveCurrentUserKey(userId, privateKey, fingerprint)
KeyStore --> Panel : local key saved
Panel -> ChatApi : PUT /api/chat/e2ee/me\n{ algorithm, publicKeyJwk, fingerprint }
ChatApi -> E2eeController : upsertCurrentUserKey(...)
E2eeController -> E2eeService : upsertCurrentUserKey(...)
E2eeService -> PG : store user_chat_keys row
PG --> E2eeService : active public key persisted
E2eeService --> E2eeController : keyRegistered=true
E2eeController --> ChatApi : CurrentUserChatKeyResponse
ChatApi --> Panel : registered key metadata

Recipient -> RecipientBrowser : open encrypted chat on this device
RecipientBrowser -> Panel : same local key-generation and registration flow
Panel -> KeyStore : saveCurrentUserKey(...)
Panel -> ChatApi : PUT /api/chat/e2ee/me
ChatApi -> E2eeController
E2eeController -> E2eeService
E2eeService -> PG : store recipient public key


end

group 2. Manager publishes a room key version
Manager -> ManagerBrowser : initialize / rotate encrypted room key
ManagerBrowser -> Panel : publishEncryptedRoomKey()
Panel -> ChatApi : GET /api/spaces/{spaceId}/chat/e2ee/recipients
ChatApi -> E2eeController : listRecipients(...)
E2eeController -> E2eeService : listRecipients(...)
E2eeService -> PG : load current participant set + public keys
PG --> E2eeService : recipients + public keys
E2eeService --> E2eeController : recipient list
E2eeController --> ChatApi : recipient metadata
ChatApi --> Panel : recipients
Panel -> Panel : generateSpaceRoomKey()
loop for each recipient
  Panel -> Panel : deriveRecipientWrapKey()\nECDH shared secret + HKDF-SHA-256
  Panel -> Panel : wrapRoomKeyForRecipient()\nAES-GCM wrap with fresh nonce
end
Panel -> ChatApi : POST /api/spaces/{spaceId}/chat/e2ee/key-versions\n{ keyVersion, rotationReason, recipients[] }
ChatApi -> E2eeController : publishKeyVersion(...)
E2eeController -> E2eeService : publishKeyVersion(...)
E2eeService -> PG : validate participant set,\nregistered keys, and next key version
E2eeService -> PG : store space_chat_key_versions\nwith publisher public key + fingerprint
E2eeService -> PG : store space_chat_key_recipients
PG --> E2eeService : room-key metadata persisted
E2eeService --> E2eeController : publish response
E2eeController --> ChatApi : keyVersion published
ChatApi --> Panel : publish success
Panel -> KeyStore : saveRoomKey(userId, spaceId, keyVersion, roomKey)

note right of PG
Publisher public key is stored with the key version
so recipients can derive the same wrap key and
unwrap the room key locally.
end note

end

group 3. Sender encrypts and posts a message
Recipient -> RecipientBrowser : type chat message
RecipientBrowser -> Panel : sendMessage()
Panel -> ChatApi : GET /api/spaces/{spaceId}/chat/e2ee/state
ChatApi -> E2eeController : getSpaceState(...)
E2eeController -> E2eeService : getSpaceState(...)
E2eeService -> PG : load latest key version + recipient wrapped key
PG --> E2eeService : activeKeyVersion, requiresRekey, wrapped key package
E2eeService --> E2eeController : E2EE state
E2eeController --> ChatApi : state response
ChatApi --> Panel : active key state
Panel -> KeyStore : loadRoomKey(userId, spaceId, activeKeyVersion)
alt room key missing locally
  Panel -> KeyStore : loadCurrentUserKey(userId)
  Panel -> Panel : unwrapRoomKeyFromPublisher()\nECDH + HKDF-SHA-256 + AES-GCM
  Panel -> KeyStore : saveRoomKey(...)
else room key already cached
  KeyStore --> Panel : cached room key
end
Panel -> Panel : encryptSpaceChatMessage()\nAES-GCM(message, AAD={spaceId,keyVersion,contentType})
Panel -> ChatApi : POST /api/spaces/{spaceId}/chat/messages\n{ keyVersion, algorithm, nonce, ciphertext, contentType, plaintextLength }
ChatApi -> ChatController : createMessage(...)
ChatController -> ChatService : createMessage(...)
ChatService -> PG : validate active key version and requiresRekey=false
ChatService -> Mongo : store encrypted message envelope
Mongo --> ChatService : ciphertext message persisted
ChatService --> ChatController : SpaceChatMessageResponse
ChatController --> ChatApi : created message envelope
ChatApi --> Panel : created encrypted message

note right of ChatService
Backend validates:
- no plaintext body in encrypted mode
- algorithm = AES_GCM_256
- active key version matches
- requiresRekey is false
- plaintextLength within configured limit
end note

end

group 4. Recipient fetches and decrypts messages
Recipient -> RecipientBrowser : open / refresh chat history
RecipientBrowser -> Panel : loadInitial() / pollLatest() / loadOlder()
Panel -> ChatApi : GET /api/spaces/{spaceId}/chat/messages
ChatApi -> ChatController : listMessages(...)
ChatController -> ChatService : listMessages(...)
ChatService -> Mongo : query mixed legacy + encrypted messages
Mongo --> ChatService : message page
ChatService --> ChatController : SpaceChatMessagePageResponse
ChatController --> ChatApi : page response
ChatApi --> Panel : mixed message page
loop for each message
  alt encrypted message envelope present
    Panel -> KeyStore : loadRoomKey(userId, spaceId, keyVersion)
    alt room key available
      Panel -> Panel : decryptSpaceChatMessage()\nAES-GCM decrypt with same AAD
      Panel -> RecipientBrowser : render decrypted plaintext
    else no room key available
      Panel -> RecipientBrowser : render safe undecryptable placeholder
    end
  else legacy plaintext message
    Panel -> RecipientBrowser : render plaintext body
  end
end

note right of RecipientBrowser
Current implementation supports mixed history:
- legacy plaintext messages may still be visible
- encrypted messages are decrypted locally when
  the active room key can be resolved
end note

end

group 5. Membership change triggers rekey
Manager -> ManagerBrowser : add or remove a student from the space
ManagerBrowser -> E2eeService : membership change via SpaceService
E2eeService -> PG : mark latest key version requiresRekey=true
PG --> E2eeService : rekey flag persisted
RecipientBrowser -> Panel : attempt to send another encrypted message
Panel -> ChatApi : GET /api/spaces/{spaceId}/chat/e2ee/state
ChatApi -> E2eeController
E2eeController -> E2eeService
E2eeService -> PG : load latest key version
PG --> E2eeService : requiresRekey=true
E2eeService --> E2eeController : state requires rekey
E2eeController --> ChatApi
ChatApi --> Panel : send blocked until new room key version is published
Panel -> RecipientBrowser : show rekey-required state
end

note over Manager,Mongo
Server-visible metadata still includes sender, space, time,
keyVersion, contentType, and plaintextLength.
The implementation provides content confidentiality,
not full metadata confidentiality.
end note

@enduml

